<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Heat from fire stimulates germination in lighted conditions (Keeley 1987b), though it is not necessary. In addition, shrubs can sprout and vigorously grow after light to moderate fire.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (20-50+ years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Seasonality</td>
			<td>Late summer-fall
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Size/extent</td>
			<td>Medium to large—up to or beyond stand size
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
